###############################################################################
### Notes
###############################################################################
# - ValuesController is excluded: its class name is `ValuesControllerController`
#   (a leftover typo), so its route is `api/ValuesControllerController`. Not used
#   by anything. Safe to delete.
# - ContactsController requires no auth (the [Authorize] is commented out per
#   AGENTS.md), so you can hit it without a token. Interactions, Admin, and
#   Deduplication do require auth.
# - Admin token is reused for everything; create a non-admin user via
#   POST /api/admin/users to test 403 paths.
# - Variables like @adminToken and @*Id are resolved at request time, not edit
#   time, so don't worry if they look like placeholders in the editor.
